      "text": "It happens on a hot afternoon. Tiberius Gracchus stands for re-election as tribune — technically illegal, but the crowd adores him. Rumors fly through the Forum: *He wants to be king! He's seizing power!*\n\nThen the senators come. Not with arguments. Not with vetoes. With chair legs and clubs.\n\nA mob of senators and their hired thugs surges into the Forum. Theo sees Nasica at their head, his toga pulled over his head like a priest performing a sacrifice. They fall on Tiberius and his supporters. The first **tribune** to be murdered in office crumples on the steps of the Capitol.\n\nThree hundred of his supporters die with him. Their bodies are thrown into the Tiber without burial rites.\n\nTheo stands frozen in the Forum as the blood dries on the stones. A voice beside him — the old fig seller from the Palatine — says quietly: 'I told you. The rich always win.'\n\nBut do they? The question burns. And Theo feels time shifting again, pulling him forward through the years like a river current.",
